# TextField

IDS Text Fields allow users to input, edit, and select text or numeric values.
Input fields validate input, provide suggestions, and help users fix errors.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/text-field
```

```tsx
import { TextField } from '@ids-ts/text-field';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `addonAfter` | `ReactElement` | No | Sets Icon/ addonAfter for the field |
| `addonBefore` | `ReactElement` | No | Sets Icon/ addonBefore for the field |
| `assignInputRef` | `(c: HTMLInputElement | null) => void` | No | - |
| `assignLabelRef` | `(c?: HTMLElement | null) => void` | No | Get reference to the label element |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | Sets data-automation-id on the input for testing |
| `disabled` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `errorText` | `string` | No | Error message to be rendered |
| `hasWeightedLabel` | `boolean` | No | Boolean flag to allow label to be bold |
| `footerTextClass` | `string` | No | Class to be applied to all the footer text (validation & helper) |
| `infoText` | `string` | No | Info message to be rendered |
| `ghostText` | `string` | No | - |
| `helperText` | `React.ReactNode` | No | Text to be display for extra information |
| `hideArrows` | `boolean` | No | Hide Arrows in the number type input element |
| `icon` | `ReactElement` | No | - |
| `iconPosition` | `'right' | 'left'` | No | - |
| `id` | `string` | No | Id of the input |
| `label` | `string` | No | - |
| `labelAddOnAfter` | `ReactNode` | No | * Label Add On After component |
| `onBlur` | `FocusEventHandler` | No | Callback fired when the input loses focus (blurs) |
| `onFocus` | `FocusEventHandler` | No | Callback fired when the input receives focus |
| `placeholder` | `string` | No | Placeholder label displayed in the field |
| `type` | `'text' \| 'tel' \| 'number' \| 'email' \| 'password'` | No | Input type. Defaults to `'text'`. |
| `validationError` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `value` | `number | string` | No | Input value |
| `warningText` | `string` | No | Warning message to be rendered |
| `readOnly` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `disableReadOnlyStyle` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `size` | `'small' | 'medium'` | No | - |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface TextFieldProps
  extends Omit<ThemeableElement<'input'>, 'size'> {
  /** Sets Icon/ addonAfter for the field */
  addonAfter?: ReactElement;
  /** Sets Icon/ addonBefore for the field */
  addonBefore?: ReactElement;
  /** Surfaces a label to assistive technology (critical when no `label` is supplied) */
  'aria-label'?: string;
  /**
   * Get reference to the input field
   *
   * @deprecated Use ref instead
   */
  assignInputRef?: (c: HTMLInputElement | null) => void;
  /** Get reference to the label element */
  assignLabelRef?: (c?: HTMLElement | null) => void;
  /** Sets data-automation-id on the input for testing */
  automationId?: string;
  /**
   * Sets the input in a disabled state when true
   *
   * @default false
   */
  disabled?: boolean;
  /** Error message to be rendered */
  errorText?: string;
  /** Boolean flag to allow label to be bold */
  hasWeightedLabel?: boolean;
  /** Class to be applied to all the footer text (validation & helper) */
  footerTextClass?: string;
  /** Info message to be rendered */
  infoText?: string;
  /**
   * Ghost text (like a placeholder, but controllable)
   *
   * @deprecated Use a placeholder
   */
  ghostText?: string;
  /** Text to be display for extra information */
  helperText?: React.ReactNode;
  /** Hide Arrows in the number type input element */
  hideArrows?: boolean;
  /**
   * Prop to set desired Icon on textfield (this Icon is from the Icons-v3 component)
   *
   * @deprecated Use addOnBefore or addOnAfter
   */
  icon?: ReactElement;
  /**
   * Position of the icon
   *
   * @deprecated Use addOnBefore or addOnAfter
   * @default 'right'
   */
  iconPosition?: 'right' | 'left';
  /** Id of the input */
  id?: string;
  /**
   * Label to be displayed for the field
   *
   * @default ''
   */
  label?: string;
  /**
   * Label Add On After component
   */
  labelAddOnAfter?: ReactNode;
  /** Callback fired when the input loses focus (blurs) */
  onBlur?: FocusEventHandler;
  /** Callback fired when the input receives focus */
  onFocus?: FocusEventHandler;
  /** Placeholder label displayed in the field */
  placeholder?: string;
  /**
   * Input type (such as: text, tel, number)
   *
   * @default 'text'
   */
  type?: string;
  /**
   * Renders warning message
   *
   * @default false
   */
  validationError?: boolean;
  /** Input value */
  value?: number | string;
  /** Warning message to be rendered */
  warningText?: string;
  /**
   * Sets the input in a read-only state when true
   *
   * @default false
   */
  readOnly?: boolean;
  /**
   * Prevents CSS selector to be added for read-only styling
   *
   * @default false
   */
  disableReadOnlyStyle?: boolean;
  /**
   * Size of rendered text inside of the input
   *
   * @default 'medium'
   */
  size?: 'small' | 'medium';
}
```

</details>

## Token Usage

### Color

**container** — Container background, border, and surface colors
- `--color-container-background-accent`
- `--color-container-background-accent-active`
- `--color-container-background-accent-focus`

**text** — Primary and secondary text colors
- `--color-text-accent`
- `--color-text-complementary`
- `--color-text-disabled`

### Space

**container** — Container padding and internal spacing
- `--space-container-padding-large`
- `--space-container-padding-medium`
- `--space-container-padding-small`

### Radius

**radius** — Border radius for container corners
- `--radius-0`
- `--radius-10`
- `--radius-20`

### Font

**font** — Font family, size, weight, and line height
- `--font-size-12`
- `--font-size-14`
- `--font-size-16`

## Usage Patterns

### Basic

```tsx
(props: { theme: ThemeType }) => {
  const { theme } = props;

  return <TextField theme={theme} label="Name" id="textfield-basic" />;
}
```

### No Visible Label Use Aria Label For Accessibility

```tsx
(props: {
  theme: ThemeType;
}) => {
  const { theme } = props;

  return (
    <div>
      <h3>No Visible Label Example</h3>
      <TextField
        theme={theme}
        placeholder="Apt or Suite no"
        aria-label="Shipping Address"
        id="textfield-basic"
      />
      <p>
        The element is used to associate a text label with a form field. The
        label is used to tell users the value that should be entered in the
        associated input field. If your design does not include a visible label,
        then you must include an aria-label to provide information to the screen
        reader.
      </p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

